{
  "stem": "2718.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They're very-- made from very rough paper.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know if here in Australia-- I haven't touched a cement bag, but neither do I have any intentions, despite of the fact that I'm in the building industry as well.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But cement bags, I don't want to touch.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But the cement bags were, were rough.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after a few days-- and we saw whoever, whoever, whoever could was really trying to get up on the truck, because he didn't have to carry.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "All you have to do is to get the bag of cement and put it onto a person's shoulder.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But after a few days, we had no skin left on our fingers, and there was no medication.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So we very soon found out that, that, that cushy-- that cushion job of not having to carry the bag is not so good after all.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] everybody had to do it because nobody-- you know, there was still some sort of solidarity.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was somewhat better than it was in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was solidarity in the camp, and people were trying to help each other.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I must say it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "When we were together with my father, and we went out to work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We were marched out to work, and came back from work together, and slept next to each other.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we were trying to-- we were trying to, to look after each other, naturally like, like any-- everybody else would between a father and son.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] Anyway [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] what happened was one day my father developed eczema.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And eczema in Germany is called [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That was towards the end of November.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that was from, from malnutrition.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
